chart_description: This chart shows the length of the internal active remote delivery queue of the Exchange transport. The queue length is measured in messages.

dimension_descriptions.high: The number of messages in the queue that are in the high priority state.
dimension_descriptions.low: The number of messages in the queue that are in the low priority state.
dimension_descriptions.none: The number of messages in the queue that are not in any priority state.
dimension_descriptions.normal: The number of messages in the queue that are in the normal priority state.
